  "body": "https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/46597 brought us HostPath volume plugin that scans the host filesystem using direct calls or wrapped with nsenter when kubelet runs in a container.\r\n\r\nIMO, volume plugins should not care much if they run in a container or not, access to files / directories should be handler either by `VolumeHost` or `mount.Interface`. Especially `mount.Interface` has an implementation that knows if it runs in a container and calls nsenter when necessary.\r\n\r\n`mount.Interface` already has [method](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/util/mount/mount.go#L66) to probe if a file is a device or not, so it could be extended to check for other types of special files and `mkdir` that HostPath needs. `mount.Interface` is not a public interface so we can refactor it as we want.\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n/sig storage\r\ncc @dixudx",
